      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SNAKE AND LADDER (7) was below best last time when seventh at this track but prior to that was a Grade 4/5 winner in the quickest time on the card at this track. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Better than last run and makes appeal this time. LUNA ANNE (1) has a strong record this track and trip with 25 wins and 17 placings from 61 starts. Hit the frame latest (17.30) when third at this track in a NG. Can hit the frame with the right run. SHAMROCK LADY (2) was in the money again last time and not beaten far when third (20.73) at Grafton in a Grade 5. Safe beginner who should be prominent to the first bend. Expected to bounce back to best. MID CITY BOSS (6) profiles nicely here at this trip.",
